						<summary>

						<p>Parapet wall to the right of entrance into the Sabhāmaṇṭapa of the Sōmēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>12th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This inscription is engraved below three groups of sculptures. States that the sculptures depict the scenes of (i) Jēḍara Dāsimayya offering cloth to the god; (ii) Siriyāḷi-śetti and Cheṁgaḷavve offering their son to the god: (iii) god Śiva as having come down and danced before the kuṁbāra (i.e. potter) Guṁḍa. In characters of about 12th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">Ep. Ind.,</hi> Vol. XXIX p. 139 ff.</p>						

						</summary>
